{
  "description": "A close-up, dramatic view from inside a tulip flower. The image focuses intensely on the flower's reproductive parts: the pistil and stamens. The pistil is a pale, creamy yellow-green, with a distinct three-lobed stigma at the top. Surrounding the pistil are six dark brown, almost black, stamens with prominent anthers covered in pollen. The petals surrounding these structures transition from a vibrant deep red at the edges to a creamy white-yellow near the base, creating a strong contrast. The texture of the petals appears soft and delicate, with subtle folds and curves. The shallow depth of field emphasizes the central reproductive structures while blurring the petals slightly, further drawing the viewer's attention inward.",
